Class BipartiteGraph<L>

  • java.lang.Object
    • homework2.BipartiteGraph<L>

  • public class BipartiteGraph<L>
extends java.lang.Object
    A bipartite graph is a graph with a group of white nodes and a group of black nodes, while all the edges cross from one group to the other. Nodes have unique labels and edges are uniquely recognized by their label and one of their ends.
